problem.tex: Evaluate $\int_\gamma\frac{\log z}{z^2-25}dz$ where $\gamma$ is the boundary of $B_2(4)$ in positive orientation. using the principal branch of log.

solution.tex: The principal branch of log is holomorphic on the interior and boundary of the ball centered at 4 of radius 2. By Cauchy's integral formula \[\int_\gamma\frac{\frac{\log z}{z+5}}{z-5}dz=2\pi i\frac{\log 5}{5+5}=\frac{\pi i\log 5}{5}.\]
